Now let's apply the Central Limit Theorem.

\subsection{Theorem II -- Central Limit Theorem}

\begin{itemize}
\samepage
\item The histogram of averages tends to look like the normal cure even when the histogram of individuals does not (and get closer to the normal curve as the sample size get larger).
\samepage
\item The mean of the averages is the same as the mean of the individuals.
\samepage
\item The standard deviation of the averages equals the standard deviation of individuals divided by $\sqrt{n}$.
\samepage
\item Notation:  \\
\begin{equation} 
 \bar{X} \sim N\left( \mu, \frac{\sigma}{ \sqrt{n}} \right) \nonumber
 \end{equation}

\end{itemize}

